cROS 0.1
********

cRos is a library written in stadard c-language that provides a mono thread implementation of the 
basic features required to implement a ROS (Robot Operating System) node.

Requirements

cRos runs on a base Linux distribution with:
-The GCC compiler
-CMake 2.6 or later
-(Optional) Doxygen

Build cROS

cRos uses CMake the cross platform build system.
From a terminal, move inside the cros/build directory, and type the following commands:

cmake ..
make

You will find a static library (libcros.a) inside the cros/lib directory, and some test executables that 
makes use of the libcros library inside the cros/bin directory.

If you want to build the create the library documentation, type: (you need Doxygen)

make docs

You will find the html documentation inside the cros/docs/html directory. To browse the documentation, 
open with a web browser the index.html file.